    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "## Requirements\r\n\r\n1. When truffle is passed an unsupported command line flag, it should throw a helpful error.\r\n\r\nExample:\r\n```\r\ntruffle test --unsupportedFlag\r\n\r\nError: `truffle test` does not currently support the `--unsupportedFlag`.\r\nPlease see https://truffleframework.com/docs/truffle/reference/truffle-commands\r\nfor currently supported command flags.\r\n```\r\n\r\n2. Add an integration mocha test to verify proper error handling.\r\n\r\n## Prerequisite Context\r\n\r\n- Familiarity with the current entry point for Command handling: https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/blob/develop/packages/truffle-core/lib/command.js. In particular [these lines](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/blob/develop/packages/truffle-core/lib/command.js).\r\n- Familiarity with current `truffle` command integration tests, i.e. https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/blob/develop/packages/truffle-core/test/commands.js.",
